com.i2group.apollo.events.transport

Class CardChangeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.events.transport.CardChangeSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IIdentifiable

    public final class CardChangeSet
extends Object
implements IIdentifiable
    Contains all the necessary information to create or modify a Card in the Analysis Repository.

    Specifically, a card change set has the following information:

    • The identifier of the affected card
    • The provenance for the affected card
    • Information about the source of the data in the card
    • Further change sets for the property groups and properties that the affected card contains
    For the card change sets of a command that creates a card, the following validation is applied:
    • A Card with the specified identifier must not already exist in the containing Item.
    • The created Card must contain all the mandatory Propertys and PropertyGroups.
    • The created Card must contain CardProvenance.
    For the validation for a changed Card:
    • A Card with the specified identifier must already exist in the containing Item.
    • The CardChangeSet must not contain CardProvenance.
    • After applying the CardChangeSet, the Card must contain all the mandatory Propertys and PropertyGroups.
    Common validation:
    • The specified identifier for the Card must not be empty.
    • The specified identifier for the Card must not exceed the maximum permitted length of 36 bytes.
    • The specified PropertyChangeSet and PropertyGroupChangeSet must be valid, as defined by their validation rules.
    • Any specified SourceInfo must be valid, as defined by its validation rules.
    Since:
    1.0
